Interface Entry

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractEntry, File, FileLink, Folder, FolderLink, Link

    public interface Entry
    Interface for entries in a file system.
    Author:
    Giovanni Cardenas

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static java.lang.String SEPARATOR
      Constant for the separator between a folder and its entry in the textual representation of a path.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      FileSystem getFileSystem()
      Returns the file system for this entry.
      java.lang.String getName()
      Returns the name of the entry.
      Folder getParentFolder()
      Returns the parent folder, i.e., the folder in which this entry is stored.
      java.lang.String getPath()
      Returns the full path of this entry in the folder structure.
      int getSize()
      Returns the total size of all files at or below this Entry in the folder structure.
      boolean isInFileSystem()
      Returns whether this entry is in the file system.
      void remove()
      Removes an entry from the folder structure of the file system.

      • getName

        Returns the name of the entry.

      • getParentFolder

        Folder getParentFolder()
        Returns the parent folder, i.e., the folder in which this entry is stored.
        Returns:
        the parent folder, i.e., the folder in which this entry is stored; null means that this entry is the root folder

      • getPath

        java.lang.String getPath()
        Returns the full path of this entry in the folder structure. Paths to entries that can contain entries (e.g., folders and links to folders) end with SEPARATOR; paths to entries that cannot contain other entries (e.g., files and links to files) do not end with SEPARATOR.
        Returns:
        the full path of this entry in the folder structure

      • getSize

        int getSize()
        Returns the total size of all files at or below this Entry in the folder structure.
        Returns:
        the total size of all files at or below this Entry in the folder structure

      • isInFileSystem

        boolean isInFileSystem()
        Returns whether this entry is in the file system. An entry may have been removed by a remove operation at or above the entry.
        Returns:
        whether this entry is in the file system

      • remove

        void remove()
        Removes an entry from the folder structure of the file system. Has no effect if the entry has already been removed directly or indirectly. If the method is called on a root folder, an IllegalArgumentException is thrown.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if this entry is a root folder.
